THE Newly promoted Dodoma Jiji FC have estimated a 1bn/- budget to enable them participate successfully in the new season and their team cost for the whole season. This was said here by the club’s secretary general Fortnatus John. He further said they are now in talks with four different companies which can sponsor the team. “So far we are in talks with four different companies that can sponsor our team for this season and we have reached a good place with those companies,” John said. He further added they target to bring a competitive team that will challenge all the teams featuring in the Premier League. John said he is very grateful to Dodoma City Council, Dodoma Regional Football Association (DOREFA) and Dodoma football fraternity including fans for being with their team until their promotion to the top flight league.